from (values
('Gratitude That Deepens the Heart','Gratitude','Gratitude is a practice of seeing blessings clearly and returning them to Allah through worship, humility, and service. This lesson invites the group to name specific gifts and choose one concrete act of shukr this week.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Arabic ayah text.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified transliteration.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: approved translation.','Surah Al-Baqarah 2:152','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Hadith wording about gratitude and the believer.','Sahih Muslim','What is one blessing you often overlook, and how can you honor it this week?'),
('Patience Without Numbness','Patience','Sabr is not emotional shutdown. It is faithful steadiness while the heart remains alive to pain, hope, and dua. This lesson explores patience as movement toward Allah, not passive waiting.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Arabic ayah text.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified transliteration.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: approved translation.','Surah Al-Baqarah 2:153','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Hadith wording about patience at the first strike.','Sahih al-Bukhari','Where are you being invited to practice patience without becoming hard?'),
('Intentions at the Beginning','Intention','Every action has an inner direction. Niyyah turns habits into worship and protects good deeds from becoming performance. This week, the group reflects on beginning again with sincerity.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Arabic ayah text.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified transliteration.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: approved translation.','Surah Al-Bayyinah 98:5','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Hadith wording: actions are by intentions.','Sahih al-Bukhari and Sahih Muslim','What ordinary action could you renew with a clearer intention?'),
('The Mercy of Forgiveness','Forgiveness','Seeking forgiveness restores motion to the heart. This lesson centers repentance as hope, not shame, and invites members to release despair over past mistakes.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Arabic ayah text.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified transliteration.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: approved translation.','Surah Az-Zumar 39:53','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Hadith wording about Allah rejoicing at repentance.','Sahih Muslim','What would change if you treated tawbah as a doorway rather than a courtroom?'),
('Knowledge That Becomes Light','Knowledge','Islam honors knowledge that humbles and transforms. This lesson asks how learning can move from information into worship, character, and service.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Arabic ayah text.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified transliteration.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: approved translation.','Surah Taha 20:114','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Hadith wording about the path to knowledge.','Sahih Muslim','What is one piece of beneficial knowledge you want to live, not just know?'),
('Justice Even When It Costs','Justice','Justice is a form of worship that resists ego, favoritism, and convenience. This lesson explores fairness in speech, family, work, and community life.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Arabic ayah text.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified transliteration.','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: approved translation.','Surah An-Nisa 4:135','CONTENT REVIEW REQUIRED: verified Hadith wording about helping the oppressed and preventing oppression.','Sahih al-Bukhari','Where can you be more just in a small but real way this week?'),
